2023-24 | Junior

Played in 27 of 27 games, started three … Scored a total of 57 points for an average of 1.6 per game, including a season-high of nine points in a loss at Montana State Billings … Grabbed 43 rebounds for an average of 1.6 per game … Shot 20-72 from the floor for a field goal percentage of .278, added seven made three-pointers … Shot 10-15 from the free throw line for a free throw percentage of .667 on the season … Added 31 assists … Second leading in steals for the Nanooks with 21 and three blocks

2022-23 | Sophomore

Played in 25 games for the Nanooks in her first season with the blue and gold ... Started in four games ... Van Dyke scored 68 points on the season for an average of 2.7 points per game ... She shot 35.4% from the floor, going 23-65 on the season ... From deep, she made six three-pointers, going 6-13 to shoot 46.2% ... From the free-throw line, Van Dyke went 16-20, shooting 80% ... She added 49 rebounds on the season for an average of 2.0 per game ... She grabbed 25 offensive boards and 24 defensive ... Jayda dished 41 assists, picked up 22 steals and blocked one shot

Prior to Alaska

Salt Lake Community College/Independence Community College

Following high school, Van Dyke made stops at Salt Lake Community college and Independence Community College. At Salt Lake played in 15 games before transfering to Independence Community College. There she played in 24 games and averaged 3.5 steals per game.

Herriman High School

Jayda went to Herriman High School in Herriman, Utah before graduating in 2020.

Personal

Daughter of Janel and Barry Van Dyke ... Has four siblings, Leavell, Jalyn, Brantyn and Bayler ... Janel, her mom, played basketball and volleyball at Black Hills State, Barry, her dad, played basketball at Black Hills State and Jalyn currently plays basketball at St. Paul Concordia ... Jayda is studying Business Administration
